<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project>
  <meta>
    <id>chatbot-demo</id>
    <title>GskiFlix Support Chatbot</title>
    <subtitle>A conversational AI support agent demonstrating multi-turn dialogue design, intent modeling, and escalation logic</subtitle>
    <client>GskiFlix</client>
    <role>Conversation Designer</role>
    <thumbnail>/assets/images/chatbot-demo-card.jpg</thumbnail>
    <teaser>A working AI chatbot that handles customer support scenarios for a fictional streaming service, demonstrating conversation design, prompt engineering, and escalation patterns.</teaser>
    <tags>
      <tag>AI / LLM</tag>
      <tag>GenAI</tag>
      <tag>Conversational Design</tag>
      <tag>Content Design</tag>
      <tag>UX Writing</tag>
      <tag>Content Strategy</tag>
      <tag>Prototyping</tag>
      <tag>Interactive</tag>
    </tags>
  </meta>

  <summary>
    A live conversational AI demo for GskiFlix, a fictional streaming service. This chatbot handles common support scenarios — login issues, billing disputes, playback troubleshooting, plan changes, and content discovery — with designed dialogue flows, guardrails, and escalation logic.
  </summary>

  <content>
    <section>
      <heading>Professional Context</heading>
      <body><![CDATA[
<div class="info-box info-box--note">
  <div class="info-box__header"></div>
  <div class="info-box__body">
    <p>This demo is representative of conversation design work done on the <strong>AWS Partner Assistant</strong>, an AI-powered chatbot in the AWS Marketplace Console that helps partners navigate programs, find documentation, and troubleshoot issues.</p>
    <p>The Partner Assistant is available to AWS Partners through the AWS Console. You can see instructions for accessing it in the <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/marketplace/latest/userguide/partner-assistant.html#how-to-use-partner-assistant" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AWS documentation</a>.</p>
    <p>Since the Partner Assistant requires AWS Console access, the demo below provides a publicly accessible example of the same conversation design principles applied to a fictional streaming service support scenario.</p>
  </div>
</div>
]]></body>
    </section>

    <section>
      <heading>Try the Chatbot</heading>
      <body><![CDATA[
<div class="chatbot-demo" id="chatbot-demo">
  <div class="chatbot-demo__container">
    <div class="chatbot-demo__header">
      <div class="chatbot-demo__header-info">
        <span class="chatbot-demo__header-name">GskiFlix Support</span>
        <span class="chatbot-demo__header-status">Online</span>
      </div>
      <button class="chatbot-demo__restart" id="chatbot-restart" type="button" title="Start over">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M1 4v6h6M23 20v-6h-6"/>
          <path d="M20.49 9A9 9 0 0 0 5.64 5.64L1 10m22 4l-4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 1 3.51 15"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="chatbot-demo__messages" id="chatbot-messages" role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-label="Chat messages">
    </div>

    <div class="chatbot-demo__suggestions" id="chatbot-suggestions">
      <p class="chatbot-demo__suggestions-label">Try asking about:</p>
      <div class="chatbot-demo__suggestion-chips">
        <button class="chatbot-demo__chip" type="button" data-message="I can't log into my account">I can't log in</button>
        <button class="chatbot-demo__chip" type="button" data-message="I was charged after I cancelled my subscription">Unexpected charge</button>
        <button class="chatbot-demo__chip" type="button" data-message="My show keeps buffering and won't play">Buffering issues</button>
        <button class="chatbot-demo__chip" type="button" data-message="How do I change my plan?">Change my plan</button>
        <button class="chatbot-demo__chip" type="button" data-message="I can't find a show I was watching">Can't find a show</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chatbot-demo__input-area">
      <label for="chatbot-input" class="sr-only">Type your message</label>
      <textarea
        class="chatbot-demo__input"
        id="chatbot-input"
        rows="1"
        placeholder="Type your message..."
        aria-label="Type your message"
      ></textarea>
      <button class="chatbot-demo__send" id="chatbot-send" type="button" aria-label="Send message">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M22 2L11 13M22 2l-7 20-4-9-9-4 20-7z"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script src="/assets/js/chatbot-demo.js"></script>
]]></body>
    </section>
  </content>
</project>
